<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10561842>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Puparia of Tetralicia species. A) debarroi Martin & Carver, B) erianthi Danzig, C) graminicola Bink-Moenen, D) iberiaca Bink-Moenen, E) tuberculata Bink-Moenen, F) cecropiae (Carapia-Ruiz, 2020b) G) cecropiae Bondar (type, MZU), H) cecropiae (type, USNM), I) cecropiae (type, Bondar 1923)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10561842/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10567463>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Puparia of Tetralicia species. A) laingi (Drews & Sampson), B) mexicana (Carapia-Ruiz & Sánchez-Flores), C) mixteca (Carapia-Ruiz), D) nevadensis (Dooley), E) nigrans (Bemis), F) oblanceolata (Drews & Sampson), G) ornata (Drews & Sampson), H) pallida, I) palidonigrans (Carapia-Ruiz & Sánchez-Flores), J) petensis (Carapia-Ruiz & García-Ochaeta), K) popocatepetl (Carapia-Ruiz & Sánchez-Flores), L) pseudogranulata (Carapia-Ruiz & Sánchez-Flores), M) rotunda Baker, N) sampsoni (Sanchez-Flores & Carapia-Ruiz), O) sierrae Sampson), P) xalapensis (Sánchez-Flores & Carapia-Ruiz)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10567463/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10567459>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Puparia of Tetralicia species. A) abnormis (Quaintance), B) acaudata (Drews & Sampson), C) anahuac (Carapia- Ruiz & Sánchez-Flores), D) annonae (Carapia-Ruiz & Sánchez-Flores), E) bidentata (Sánchez-Flores & Carapia-Ruiz), F) caudata (Sánchez-Flores & Carapia-Ruiz), G. ceanothi Sampson, H) chamaedoreaelegans (Sánchez-Flores & Carapia-Ruiz), I) coachellensis (Drews & Sampson), J) eriogonum (Carapia-Ruiz), K) fourqueriasplendens (Carapia-Ruiz & Sánchez-Flores), L) granulata Sampson & Drews, M) guazumae (Carapia-Ruiz & Sánchez-Flores), N) guerrerensis (Carapia-Ruíz & Sánchez- Flores), O) hyptisemoryi (Gill), P) kobei (Sánchez-Flores & García-Ochaeta)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10567459/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10561840>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Tetralicia ericae Harrison, 1917. (A–E) puparia: A) habitus drawing, B) habitus slide specimen, C) abdomen, D) vasiform orifice slide specimen, E) vasiform orifice drawing; (F–K) adult male: F) habitus, G–H) genitalia, I–K) antennae; (L–P) adult female: L) habitus, M–N) ovipositor; O–P) antennae. Sources: A, E, H, I, J, N (Bink-Moenen, 1989); B, C, D, F, G, K, L, M, P (USNM specimen)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10561840/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10561836>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Tetralicia sawyeri n. sp. puparium. A) drawing with detail of vasiform orifice. Setae: Cs1 (cephalic setae), Ts2 (mesothoracic setae), Ts3 (metathoracic setae), As8 (8th abdominal segment setae), Cas (caudal setae); Structure: lms (longitudinal molting suture), cl (cluster of pores), def (deflexed margin), radius, tms (transverse molting suture), tm (true margin), vo (vasiform orifice), op (operculum), cp (caudal protuberance); B) puparium treated only with hydrogen peroxide; C) puparium treated with potassium hydroxide (10%) and hydrogen peroxide." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10561836/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10561844>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Tetralicia sawyeri n. sp. puparium. A) habitus drawing, B) habitus slide mounted specimen, C) lateral margin (tm=true margin), D) vasiform orifice, E) cephalothorax (sms=submarginal setae; gp=geminate pores, cl=cluster of bright pores, F) abdomen (ad=abdominal depression, gp=geminate pores, bp=bright pores, G–K) vasiform orifice (vo) showing lingula with strongly chitinized, four finger-like projections at its apex and views at different depths of field, showing the muscles responsible for the movement of the operculum (op)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10561844/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10561846>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Tetralicia sawyeri n. sp. A) adults on avocado leaf; B–H) adult female: B) antenna, C) antenna, F3–F7 =flagellar segments 3–7, rs=round sensoriae, sc=sensorial cone, D) tibia I, E) tibia II, tb=tibial brush, F) tibia III, tc=tibial comb, G) ovipositor, ov=ovipositor, H) cg=cement gland." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10561846/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

